<div class="intro">
  <h2 class="intro__title">Up and Running in 5 Minutes</h2>
  <p class="intro__description">
    Clone the repo, run the install script, and start building with Claude Code.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="steps">
  <!-- Step 1 -->
  <div class="step">
    <div class="step__number">1</div>
    <h3 class="step__title">Clone the Repository</h3>
    <p class="step__description">
      Open Terminal (find it in Applications > Utilities) and run these commands:
    </p>
    <div class="step__code">
      <code>git clone https://github.com/erikaflowers/investiture.git
cd investiture</code>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 2 -->
  <div class="step">
    <div class="step__number">2</div>
    <h3 class="step__title">Run the Install Script</h3>
    <p class="step__description">
      This single command installs everything you need: Homebrew, Node.js, project dependencies, and creates your CLAUDE.md file.
    </p>
    <div class="step__code">
      <code>./install.sh</code>
    </div>
    <div class="step__note">
      If you see "Permission denied," run <code>chmod +x install.sh</code> first, then try again.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 3 -->
  <div class="step">
    <div class="step__number">3</div>
    <h3 class="step__title">Start Your App</h3>
    <p class="step__description">
      Launch the development server. Your app will open automatically in your browser.
    </p>
    <div class="step__code">
      <code>npm start</code>
    </div>
    <div class="step__note">
      Opens at <a href="http://localhost:3000" target="_blank">http://localhost:3000</a>. When you edit files, the browser updates automatically.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 4 -->
  <div class="step">
    <div class="step__number">4</div>
    <h3 class="step__title">Open Claude Code</h3>
    <p class="step__description">
      Open Claude Code in your project folder. It will read the CLAUDE.md file automatically and understand your project structure.
    </p>
    <div class="step__code">
      <code>claude</code>
    </div>
    <div class="step__note">
      Make sure you're still in the investiture directory when you launch Claude Code.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 5 -->
  <div class="step">
    <div class="step__number">5</div>
    <h3 class="step__title">Start Building</h3>
    <p class="step__description">
      Try one of these prompts in Claude Code. Your app updates in real time as Claude makes changes.
    </p>
    <div class="step__code">
      <code>"Add a color picker that changes the page background"

"Add a todo list with add and delete"

"Add a dark/light mode toggle that remembers my preference"</code>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

